node.text:
This guy is wonderful and it makes me sick to my stomach when he talks about the things that he saw that day. The worst possible people stormed the Capitol on January 6th. Privileged, entitled, and presumptuous that they were just going to walk in and no one would try to stop them.

Turns out every officer there wasn’t the kind of officer that would remove  barricades for them and unlock doors. They were enough of those, but I’m thankful this guy wasn’t one of them. But it sure sounds like they put them through hell.

node.text:
A, that woman is an absolute queen.

B, I wish someone would tell me to get back on my highway to hell, just once. I would fall over laughing right in front of them. That’s hilarious and the fact he’s about to have a coronary because they were short on baskets, is just beyond..

node.title: Get back on your highway to hell! 🤣

There is only one reason you say something like that out loud in a room full of people and that is because you know that you’re in a place where it will be accepted. 

It is disgusting language and behavior and the fact that the man who is speaking at the podium didn’t even flinch when it happened, and he still vouched for that guy, tells you everything you need to know. The good people in that community are out numbered. #Alabama #TommyBryant

node.text:
What Bryan Stevenson and the @eji_org are doing, not only in Montgomery, but around the country, is amazing. If you don’t know much about @eji_org, please look into them. Entrance to the Legacy Museum and the Memorial for Peace and Justice, is free. But there is a donation box inside the lobby in the Museum where you can donate money to help them continue their work. You can also donate through @eji_org 

This isn’t just about slavery, it’s also about segregation and mass incarceration. If you look into the innocent people the Equal Justice Initiative has gotten out of prison, off of death row, and read their stories, it is astounding. I think they’re just under 200. Start with Anthony Ray Hinton, who is represented in the museum. #EJI

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by AGirlHasNoPresident on July 31, 2021 tagging @npr. May be an image of 2 people, people standing and text that says 'The U.S. Men's Fencing Team Wore Pink Face Masks To Protest Their Own Teammate July 30, 2021 11:08 PM ET VANESSA ROMO'.

Photo by AGirlHasNoPresident on July 31, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'The American fencing team is not happy to have Alen Hadzic representing the U.S. at the Tokyo Olympics. on to the roster, Almost immediately after making the 29-year-old was accused of sexual misconduct between 2013 and 2015 by three women. Hadzic denies the allegations and successfully appealed suspension that would have kept him the U.S. team. On Friday, the men's team conveyed their displeasure to the world, wearing pink face masks support of sexual assault victims. It made for striking image as Jake Hoyle, Curtis McDowald and Yeisser Ramirez appeared in the masks, while Hadzic was the in black.'.

Photo by AGirlHasNoPresident on July 31, 2021. May be an image of 2 people and text that says 'Ibtihaj Muhammad @IbtihajMuhammad #TeamUSA men's epee team wore pink masks for their opening match at the Olympics as a show of support for sexual assault victims. Alen Hadzic their teammate accused of rape and sexual assault- is on the left. Kudos to the team for taking a stand. #BelieveWomen 9:21 AM Jul 30, 2021 from Old Greenwich, CT'.

Photo by AGirlHasNoPresident on July 31, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Jackie Dubrovich, an Olympic fencer who was in Tokyo, called the move by her teammates "PERFORMATIVE ACTIVISM" on Instagram. She called for accountability. "THE PEOPLE/ SYSTEMS WHO ENABLED & PROTECTED A VIOLENT PREDATOR ARE NOT BEING HELD ACCOUNTABLE, she wrote. "FEMALE ATHLETES WERE NOT PROTECTED & OUR SAFETY WAS DEEMED UNIMPORTANT." Hadzic had been suspended from all fencing activities by the U.S. Center for SafeSport, an independent agency that investigates sexual abuse Olympic sports. But weeks later, an arbitrator ruled that the suspension was "inappropriate to the allegations,' The New York Times reported. Article continues after sponsor message'.

***I see people are attacking the girl in this video, which means they’re missing the point. Someone sent me this video that this girl made. It had nothing to do with me. I shared it because I can relate because I’m getting the same kind of messages that she’s talking about. Please stop attacking this girl and her clothes. It’s so tired.***

Someone sent this to me after I took the whole morning off for some medical stuff. It’s hilarious! 

I’m not exaggerating when I say there are no less than three messages like this in my DMs. I think people assume this upsets me, but oh my gosh, I howled with laughter. I’m not sure what response people expect when they send these things. @thedailytay #NotAnAirport

“The CDC is scheduled to publish data Friday that will back Walensky's controversial decision to change guidance for fully vaccinated people. She said Tuesday the CDC was recommending that even fully vaccinated people wear masks indoors in places where transmission of the virus is sustained or high.
And she said everyone in schools -- students, staff and visitors -- should wear masks at all times. 

But vaccinated people are safer, the document indicates.
"Vaccines prevent more than 90% of severe disease, but may be less effective at preventing infection or transmission," it reads. "Therefore, more breakthrough and more community spread despite vaccination."

It says vaccines reduce the risk of severe disease or death 10-fold and reduce the risk of infection three-fold.

The CDC, the document advises, should "acknowledge the war has changed." It recommends vaccine mandates and universal mask requirements.
The virus is once against surging across the US -- especially in areas where fewer people are vaccinated.”

node.text:
I’ve been asked several times to do a collab but until now, I never agreed. However, after a post from last week (I’ll put it in my stories) where someone felt the need to announce their departure, I was asked by @liveabove.co if I was interested, and I immediately said yes! I agreed because, I love everything they do and because this ended up being a pretty funny moment. 

These shirts were designed by @liveabove.co and the proceeds will go to benefit @crcnashville who are amazing, and they do so much to help the ppl of Nashville. Volunteering there, pre-Covid, is one of the things I miss the most. On more than one occasion, I got to see firsthand how much they help the community, especially after the tornadoes we had.

Please go check out @liveabove.co and help us raise some money for charity! I put the link in my stories and as always, I will share it on Twitter @AGirlHasNoPres 

Thank you! #LiveAbove 

They’re taking pre-orders at the link in my bio. 

*I am not a flu bot
